\sin 2x = 2 \sin x \cos x
\sin x = \sin 2x \implies 2 \sin x \cos x - \sin x = 0 \implies \sin x (2 \cos x - 1) = 0
\sin{2x}=\sin{x}\iff 2x=(-1)^nx+n\pi
x=2n\pi
x=\dfrac{(2n+1)\pi}{3}
